comment:
* A Parcelable object to handle the IMS call profile, which provides the service, call type, and * additional information related to the call. *

* See the following specifications for more information about this class: GSMA IR.92/IR.94, * 3GPP TS 24.229/TS 26.114/TS26.111. * @hide

variables.name: SERVICE_TYPE_NONE
variables.comment:
* It is for a special case. It helps that the application can make a call
     * without IMS connection (not registered).
     * In the moment of the call initiation, the device try to connect to the IMS network
     * and initiates the call.

variables.name: SERVICE_TYPE_NORMAL
variables.comment: * It is a default type and can be selected when the device is connected to the IMS network.

variables.name: SERVICE_TYPE_EMERGENCY
variables.comment: * It is for an emergency call.

variables.name: CALL_TYPE_VOICE_N_VIDEO
variables.comment: * IMSPhone to support IR.92 & IR.94 (voice + video upgrade/downgrade)

variables.name: CALL_TYPE_VOICE
variables.comment: * IR.92 (Voice only)

variables.name: CALL_TYPE_VIDEO_N_VOICE
variables.comment: * VT to support IR.92 & IR.94 (voice + video upgrade/downgrade)

variables.name: CALL_TYPE_VT
variables.comment: * Video Telephony (audio / video two way)

variables.name: CALL_TYPE_VT_TX
variables.comment: * Video Telephony (audio two way / video TX one way)

variables.name: CALL_TYPE_VT_RX
variables.comment: * Video Telephony (audio two way / video RX one way)

variables.name: CALL_TYPE_VT_NODIR
variables.comment: * Video Telephony (audio two way / video inactive)

variables.name: CALL_TYPE_VS
variables.comment: * VideoShare (video two way)

variables.name: CALL_TYPE_VS_TX
variables.comment: * VideoShare (video TX one way)

variables.name: CALL_TYPE_VS_RX
variables.comment: * VideoShare (video RX one way)

variables.name: EXTRA_CONFERENCE
variables.comment: * @hide

variables.name: EXTRA_EMERGENCY_CALL
variables.comment:
* Boolean extra property set on an {@link ImsCallProfile} to indicate that this call is an
     * emergency call.  The {@link ImsService} sets this on a call to indicate that the network has
     * identified the call as an emergency call.

variables.name: EXTRA_VMS
variables.comment: * @hide

variables.name: EXTRA_CALL_MODE_CHANGEABLE
variables.comment: * @hide

variables.name: EXTRA_CONFERENCE_AVAIL
variables.comment: * @hide

variables.name: EXTRA_OEM_EXTRAS
variables.comment:
* Extra key used to store a Bundle containing proprietary extras to send to the ImsService.
     * Use {@link #getProprietaryCallExtras()} instead.
     * @hide

variables.name: EXTRA_OIR
EXTRA_CNAP
EXTRA_DIALSTRING
EXTRA_RETRY_CALL_FAIL_REASON
variables.comment:
* This extra holds call fail cause because of which redial is attempted.
     * see {@link android.telephony.ims.ImsReasonInfo} {@code CODE_*}
     * for possible values this extra can hold.
     *
     * @hide

variables.name: EXTRA_RETRY_CALL_FAIL_NETWORKTYPE
variables.comment:
* This extra holds call network type on which lower layers
     * may try attempting redial.
     * See {@link TelephonyManager} {@code NETWORK_TYPE_*}
     * for possible values this extra can hold.
     *
     * @hide

variables.name: OIR_DEFAULT
variables.comment: "user subscription default value"

variables.name: OIR_PRESENTATION_RESTRICTED
variables.comment: * Restricted presentation for Originating Identity.

variables.name: OIR_PRESENTATION_NOT_RESTRICTED
variables.comment: * Not restricted presentation for Originating Identity.

variables.name: OIR_PRESENTATION_UNKNOWN
variables.comment: * Presentation unknown for Originating Identity.

variables.name: OIR_PRESENTATION_PAYPHONE
variables.comment: * Payphone presentation for Originating Identity.

variables.name: DIALSTRING_NORMAL
variables.comment: * A default or normal normal call.

variables.name: DIALSTRING_SS_CONF
variables.comment: * Call for SIP-based user configuration

variables.name: DIALSTRING_USSD
variables.comment: * Call for USSD message

variables.name: CALL_RESTRICT_CAUSE_NONE
variables.comment: * Call is not restricted on peer side and High Definition media is supported

variables.name: CALL_RESTRICT_CAUSE_RAT
variables.comment:
* High Definition media is not supported on the peer side due to the Radio Access Technology
     * (RAT) it is are connected to.

variables.name: CALL_RESTRICT_CAUSE_DISABLED
variables.comment: * The service has been disabled on the peer side.

variables.name: CALL_RESTRICT_CAUSE_HD
variables.comment: * High definition media is not currently supported.

variables.name: EXTRA_OI
variables.comment:
* String extra properties
     *  oi : Originating identity (number), MT only
     *  cna : Calling name
     *  ussd : For network-initiated USSD, MT only
     *  remote_uri : Connected user identity (it can be used for the conference)
     *  ChildNum: Child number info.
     *  Codec: Codec info.
     *  DisplayText: Display text for the call.
     *  AdditionalCallInfo: Additional call info.
     *  CallPull: Boolean value specifying if the call is a pulled call.

variables.name: EXTRA_ADDITIONAL_SIP_INVITE_FIELDS
variables.comment:
* String extra property
     *  Containing fields from the SIP INVITE message for an IMS call

variables.name: EXTRA_CALL_DISCONNECT_CAUSE
variables.comment:
* CallDisconnectCause: Specify call disconnect cause. This extra should be a code
     * corresponding to ImsReasonInfo and should only be populated in the case that the
     * call has already been missed

variables.name: EXTRA_CALL_RAT_TYPE
variables.comment:
* Extra key which the RIL can use to indicate the radio technology used for a call.
     * Valid values are:
     * {@link android.telephony.ServiceState#RIL_RADIO_TECHNOLOGY_LTE},
     * {@link android.telephony.ServiceState#RIL_RADIO_TECHNOLOGY_IWLAN}, and the other defined
     * {@code RIL_RADIO_TECHNOLOGY_*} constants.
     * Note: Despite the fact the {@link android.telephony.ServiceState} values are integer
     * constants, the values passed for the {@link #EXTRA_CALL_RAT_TYPE} should be strings (e.g.
     * "14" vs (int) 14).
     * Note: This is used by {@link com.android.internal.telephony.imsphone.ImsPhoneConnection#
     *      updateImsCallRatFromExtras(Bundle)} to determine whether to set the
     * {@link android.telecom.TelecomManager#EXTRA_CALL_NETWORK_TYPE} extra value and
     * {@link android.telecom.Connection#PROPERTY_WIFI} property on a connection.
     * @deprecated the constants associated with this extra are hidden, instead use
     * {@link #EXTRA_CALL_NETWORK_TYPE}.

variables.name: EXTRA_CALL_NETWORK_TYPE
variables.comment:
* Extra key with an {@code int} value which can be set in {@link #setCallExtraInt(String, int)} * to indicate the network type used for a call. *

* Valid values are defined by {@code TelephonyManager.NETWORK_TYPE_*} constants. An example may * be {@link android.telephony.TelephonyManager#NETWORK_TYPE_LTE}.

variables.name: EXTRA_CALL_RAT_TYPE_ALT
variables.comment:
* Similar to {@link #EXTRA_CALL_RAT_TYPE}, except with a lowercase 'c'.  Used to ensure
     * compatibility with modems that are non-compliant with the {@link #EXTRA_CALL_RAT_TYPE}
     * extra key.  Should be removed when the non-compliant modems are fixed.
     * @hide
     * @deprecated Use {@link #EXTRA_CALL_NETWORK_TYPE} instead.

variables.name: EXTRA_FORWARDED_NUMBER
variables.comment:
* String extra property containing forwarded numbers associated with the current connection
     * for an IMS call. The value is string array, and it can include multiple numbers, and
     * the array values are expected E164 (e.g. +1 (650) 253-0000) format.

variables.name: mServiceType
variables.comment: @hide

variables.name: mCallType
variables.comment: @hide

variables.name: mRestrictCause
variables.comment: @hide

variables.name: mCallerNumberVerificationStatus
variables.comment: * The VERSTAT for an incoming call's phone number.

variables.name: VERIFICATION_STATUS_NOT_VERIFIED
variables.comment: * Indicates that the network could not perform verification.

variables.name: VERIFICATION_STATUS_PASSED
variables.comment:
* Indicates that verification by the network passed.  This indicates there is a high likelihood
     * that the call originated from a valid source.

variables.name: VERIFICATION_STATUS_FAILED
variables.comment:
* Indicates that verification by the network failed.  This indicates there is a high likelihood
     * that the call did not originate from a valid source.

variables.name: mEmergencyServiceCategories
variables.comment:
* The emergency service categories, only valid if {@link #getServiceType} returns * {@link #SERVICE_TYPE_EMERGENCY} * * If valid, the value is the bitwise-OR combination of the following constants: *
    *
  1. {@link EmergencyNumber#EMERGENCY_SERVICE_CATEGORY_UNSPECIFIED}
    2. *
  2. {@link EmergencyNumber#EMERGENCY_SERVICE_CATEGORY_POLICE}
    3. *
  3. {@link EmergencyNumber#EMERGENCY_SERVICE_CATEGORY_AMBULANCE}
    4. *
  4. {@link EmergencyNumber#EMERGENCY_SERVICE_CATEGORY_FIRE_BRIGADE}
    5. *
  5. {@link EmergencyNumber#EMERGENCY_SERVICE_CATEGORY_MARINE_GUARD}
    6. *
  6. {@link EmergencyNumber#EMERGENCY_SERVICE_CATEGORY_MOUNTAIN_RESCUE}
    7. *
  7. {@link EmergencyNumber#EMERGENCY_SERVICE_CATEGORY_MIEC}
    8. *
  8. {@link EmergencyNumber#EMERGENCY_SERVICE_CATEGORY_AIEC}
    9. *
* * Reference: 3gpp 23.167, Section 6 - Functional description; * 3gpp 22.101, Section 10 - Emergency Calls.

variables.name: mEmergencyUrns
variables.comment:
* The emergency Uniform Resource Names (URN), only valid if {@link #getServiceType} returns
     * {@link #SERVICE_TYPE_EMERGENCY}.
     *
     * Reference: 3gpp 24.503, Section 5.1.6.8.1 - General;
     *            3gpp 22.101, Section 10 - Emergency Calls.

variables.name: mEmergencyCallRouting
variables.comment:
* The emergency call routing, only valid if {@link #getServiceType} returns * {@link #SERVICE_TYPE_EMERGENCY} * * If valid, the value is any of the following constants: *
    *
  1. {@link EmergencyNumber#EMERGENCY_CALL_ROUTING_UNKNOWN}
    2. *
  2. {@link EmergencyNumber#EMERGENCY_CALL_ROUTING_NORMAL}
    3. *
  3. {@link EmergencyNumber#EMERGENCY_CALL_ROUTING_EMERGENCY}
    4. *
